dc_title_s: Taichu, Formosa (Taiwan), Taichu Shu. A.M.S. L991
dc_description_s: AMS 1. North Decimal Degree 24.166667. South Decimal Degree 24.116667. East Decimal Degree 120.700000. West Decimal Degree 120.650000. Alternate title: Taichu. In upper left margin: Formosa city plans 1:8,000. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. Compiled from aerial photography dated from November 1943 to September 1944, by photo-planimetric method and by reference to Formosa 1:50,000, A.M.S. Sheet 2219-III, 1944; Formosa 1:25,000, A.M.S. Sheet 2210-III NE, 1944; Japanese Imperial Land Survey 1:50,000, Sheet G51-XXXI-8, 1928. Additional information from intelligence data. Place names are transcribed according to the Modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. With a glossary. Name has been changed to T'ai-chung [Taichung].
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
